The paper deals with coding theory and the existence of matrices that can be used for coding purposes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Information Theory and Probability (cs.ITP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves constructive proofs and algorithms, which could place it in the Data Structures (cs.DS) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions a class of codes proposed by Rosenbloom and Tsfasman, which could indicate a connection to Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
